## Finding: User Cohort Management for Beta Has No Coverage

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: Beta testing requires structured cohort management: which users are in closed beta, open beta, or GA? Who was invited vs. who signed up organically? Which cohort is exposed to which feature flag combination? The feature_flags skill provides a user-to-rollout hashing function but has no concept of named cohorts, allowlists, denylist exclusions, or beta program enrollment. The feedback_system has no way to segment feedback by cohort (internal team vs. design partners vs. public beta). The product_analytics skill identifies users and organizations but has no cohort tracking for beta program membership. Real-world Beta programs need: invite-only enrollment, cohort-tagged analytics, per-cohort feedback routing, and cohort-aware rate limits.
### Proposed Resolution: New skill `beta_cohort_management` (Phase 5.75): Prisma model for BetaCohort and BetaEnrollment, invitation flow with token-gated signup, cohort property attached to every analytics event, cohort-aware feedback routing, and admin dashboard for cohort progression. Trigger: "manage beta users", "beta invitations", "cohort tracking."
### Cross-Phase Impact: Without cohort management, product_analytics metrics conflate internal testing traffic with real user behavior, corrupting all dashboards. feature_flags rollout percentages have no way to target specific beta cohort members. Phase 6 community_management cannot distinguish beta testers from general users.

