## Finding: Feedback System Has No Closure Loop Back to Users

### Gap Type: SHALLOW_COVERAGE
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: The feedback_system skill has a full triage workflow (NEW → TRIAGED → IN_PROGRESS → RESOLVED → CLOSED) and admin dashboard, but zero mechanism for notifying the submitting user that their feedback was acted upon. The skill's status workflow is entirely internal. When a user submits a P1 bug and it gets resolved, they receive no email, no in-app notification, no "here's what we did" message. During Beta, feedback loop closure is the primary driver of user engagement and trust. Beta testers who report bugs and never hear back stop reporting bugs — exactly the opposite of what Beta needs. The email_templates skill has 8 templates but no "your feedback was resolved" template.
### Proposed Resolution: Extend feedback_system skill with a "User Notification" section: add a FeedbackUpdate email template to the email_templates skill, trigger it on status transitions to RESOLVED/CLOSED, include admin notes (sanitized) in the notification, and add a public changelog of resolved items to close the loop at scale. Trigger: "notify user on feedback resolution", "feedback closure email."
### Cross-Phase Impact: Low feedback closure rate → low Beta engagement → insufficient data for graduation criteria → delayed Phase 6. Also affects user_documentation in Phase 6 which should describe how the feedback process works.

