## Finding: Beta-to-GA Migration Path Is Entirely Absent

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: CRITICAL
### Evidence: There is no skill, checklist, or procedure for migrating from Beta to GA. Beta-to-GA migration involves: removing all beta-only rate limit overrides, cleaning up all temporary feature flags, migrating beta user accounts to GA plan structures, archiving beta feedback data and producing a summary report, disabling beta-only email templates (beta invitations), enabling production-grade monitoring thresholds, switching from beta pricing to GA pricing, communicating the transition to beta users via email. The Phase 5.75-Beta skills collectively produce a running Beta but have no exit procedure. The Phase 6-Handoff skills assume GA is already achieved. The gap between them is the actual migration step — which is fully uncovered.
### Proposed Resolution: New skill `beta_to_ga_migration` (Phase 5.75, exit boundary): Step-by-step migration checklist covering flag cleanup, account migration, data archival, monitoring threshold changes, pricing activation, and user communication. Produces a migration runbook artifact. Trigger: "migrate beta to GA", "graduate to production", "beta exit migration."
### Cross-Phase Impact: This is the most operationally critical gap. Without it, the transition from Phase 5.75 to Phase 6 is undefined. Teams will improvise this migration under time pressure, leading to data inconsistencies, user confusion, and monitoring gaps at exactly the moment when they are most vulnerable.

